Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State has inaugurated the State Security Network, code-named, Operation Amotekun. The governor did the inauguration on Thursday at the Pavilion Ground, Oke-Mosan, Abeokuta. Earlier, Abiodun had assured that operatives of the Amotekun corps would be deployed in the Yewa axis of the state for the security of lives and property. DAILY POST reports that the Yewa axis of Ogun State recently witnessed cases of killings, kidnapping, arson, and other clashes. The incidents, it was gathered, were as a result of farmers-herders clashes. Recall that the Amotekun corps is an initiative of governors in the South West introduced to combat kidnapping, banditry and other crimes bedevilling the region. 